l.com/www/uploads/2019/12/WhatsApp-Image-2019-12-25-at-20.32.40-400x250.jpeg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/emma-eytan1574038327-200x200.jpeg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2020/01/POPE-SLAP-e1577866668536-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/10/AP19283797496941-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/AP_19358560937905-e1577627682568-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/07/Untitled-1-1-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/AP_19364338081218-e1577799739814-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2020/01/AP_20001377932478-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/11/AP_19322221152276-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/rivka-hellendall1577843042-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/Untitled-29-e1577794068480-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/Sagi-Melamed2-1530951808-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/06/AP_19168726506578-e1560836928101-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/F191202HP23-1-e1577862787664-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/Justin-Amler-1530952515-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/Israel-Drazin1-1530953506-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/Jan_de_Bray-Judith_and_Holofernes-e1577613026251-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/01/20190122-20190122_untitled_03518-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/D34-058-e1577804105971-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/blogs/uploads/users/Shulamit-S-Magnus-1530952785-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/AP19348549377996-e1576742150973-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/F191229MIS06-1-e1577636424738-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/04/beresheet-selfie1-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/Dreidel-Guinness-2019-resize-2160x1200-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/ronen-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/2020-JTA-Election-Main-Header-e1576834196351-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/000_1ND87P-e1577818116663-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/Untitled-5-7-640x400.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/08/WhatsApp-Image-2019-08-07-at-10.56.58-AM-200x200.jpeg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/10/AP_19267503779649-200x200.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/05/AP_19140839764197-e1558662106909-400x250.jpg", "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2019/12/meir-e1577122983674-400x250.jpg"], "movies": [], "text": "The Justice Ministry\u2019s Police Internal Investigations Department filed an indictment Wednesday against a police officer who is accused of assaulting an ultra-Orthodox man by yanking on his sidelocks in an unprovoked attack as he was arresting him.\n\nThe alleged assault on Mordechai Kreuzer in July was caught on camera and published by Hebrew media, leading to a backlash of accusations of police brutality.\n\nPIID filed the indictment at the Jerusalem Magistrate\u2019s Court against Yaakov Sheetrit, who is accused of assault as well as obstruction of justice in the course of the subsequent probe.\n\nGet The Times of Israel's Daily Edition by email and never miss our top stories Free Sign Up\n\nAnother officer who was also involved in the incident will have his case dealt with by a disciplinary tribunal, Haaretz reported.\n\nThe incident happened during a demonstration against the demolition of illegal buildings in the central city of Beit Shemesh, which has a large ultra-Orthodox community.\n\n\u05ea\u05d9\u05e2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05de\u05d7\u05e8\u05d9\u05d3: \u05d1\u05dc\u05e9 \u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05d8\u05e8\u05d4 \u05db\u05de\u05e2\u05d8 \u05ea\u05d5\u05dc\u05e9 \u05d0\u05ea \u05e4\u05d0\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05e2\u05e6\u05d5\u05e8 >>>\u05d4\u05d5\u05d0 \u05dc\u05d0 \u05de\u05ea\u05e0\u05d2\u05d3 \u05dc\u05de\u05e2\u05e6\u05e8, \u05d5\u05db\u05dc\u05dc \u05dc\u05d0 \u05d4\u05e9\u05ea\u05ea\u05e3 \u05d1\u05d4\u05e4\u05d2\u05e0\u05d4 \u2013 \u05de\u05d4 \u05e9\u05db\u05de\u05d5\u05d1\u05df \u05dc\u05d0 \u05de\u05e0\u05e2 \u05de\u05d4\u05e9\u05d5\u05d8\u05e8 \u05dc\u05de\u05e9\u05d5\u05da \u05dc\u05d5 \u05d1\u05d0\u05db\u05d6\u05e8\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05d1\u05e4\u05d0\u05d5\u05ea #\u05de\u05e9\u05d8\u05e8\u05ea_\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc_2019 \u2022 \u05e9\u05ea\u05e4\u05d5 \u2013 \u05d5\u05e0\u05e9\u05d9\u05dd \u05e1\u05d5\u05e3 \u05dc\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9\u05de\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05d8\u05e8\u05ea\u05d9\u05ea! \u05e4\u05d5\u05e8\u05e1\u05dd \u05e2\u05dc \u05d9\u05d3\u05d9 \u200f\u05d7\u05d3\u05e9\u05d5\u05ea \u05db\u05d9\u05db\u05e8 \u05d4\u05e9\u05d1\u05ea\u200f \u05d1- \u05d9\u05d5\u05dd \u05e9\u05e0\u05d9, 8 \u05d1\u05d9\u05d5\u05dc\u05d9 2019\n\nSheetrit and other officers told a crowd of protesters to disperse from a parking lot and then allegedly began pushing and shoving them.\n\nAt one point their attention became focused on Kreuzer, and Sheetrit allegedly hit him in the face, then dragged him away to a patrol car, pulling him by his sidelock.\n\nDuring the clash Kreuzer suffered injuries to his face, back, elbow, forearm, shoulder and pelvis.\n\nSheetrit was also injured, apparently falling over and requiring a cast for his leg. He later claimed that Kreuzer attacked him with punches and kicks and that he was also assaulted by other demonstrators, a claim not borne out by the video evidence.\n\nKreuzer was initially arrested and charged with assaulting an officer but released after the video came to light. He said that in the hours after his arrest, which happened on a Friday, he was further mistreated by police at the jail and forced to ride in a car on Shabbat.\n\nSheetrit was suspended from duties after the investigation opened.\n\nAt the time, Public Security Minister Gilad Erdan, who had come under fire over accusation of police brutality against Ethiopian-Israelis, called the incident appalling and said he approved of the officer\u2019s suspension.\n\nInterior Minister Aryeh Deri, head of the Haredi political party Shas, said at the time the incident \u201cbordered on anti-Semitism.\u201d", "keywords": [], "meta_keywords": [""], "tags": ["Full Coverage 2019-2020 Israeli elections", "ultra-Orthodox Jews", "Beit Shemesh", "Jerusalem Magistrate's Court", "Full Coverage 2020 US presidential elections", "See All", "Police Internal Investigations Department", "Full Coverage Times of Israel podcasts", "Full Coverage Israel media review"], "authors": [], "publish_date": null, "summary": "", "article_html": "", "meta_description": "Yaakov Sheetrit accused of mistreating protester during arrest and then obstructing justice in probe of incident", "meta_lang": "en", "meta_favicon": "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/uploads/2018/11/toi_icon_512-200x200.png", "meta_data": {"viewport": "width=1024", "description": "Yaakov Sheetrit accused of mistreating protester during arrest and then obstructing justice in probe of incident", "msapplication-TileImage": "https://static.timesofisrael.com/www/images/toi_icon_144.png", "msapplication-TileColor": "#ffffff", "theme-color": "#ffffff", "fb": {"app_id": 123142304440875}, "og": {"url": "https://www.timesofisrael.com/cop-indicted-for-yanking-on-ultra-orthodox-mans-sidelock/", "type": "article", "title": "Cop indicted for yanking on ultra-Orthodox man\u2019s sidelock", "description": "Yaakov Sheetrit accused of mistreating protester during arrest and then obstructing justice in probe of incident", "image": {"identi